== Architecture ==
[[File:Torii of Toyota Jinjya in Hualien, Taiwan.JPG|thumb|200px|Torii of Toyota Shrine]]
Toyota Shrine faced north (northeast), a unique orientation compared to most south-facing shrines in Taiwan. Bilian Temple was built on the original site of the shrine’s haiden, and the torii at the intersection of Zhongshan Road and Minquan Street now serves as the temple’s entrance. The former approach, several hundred meters southwest, retains its original stone lanterns and guardian lion-dog statues. The grounds also feature a commemorative monument celebrating the 30th anniversary of the village, inscribed by {{ill|Kiyoshi Hasegawa (admiral)|en|Kiyoshi Hasegawa (admiral)|WD=Q5353732|lt=Hasegawa Kiyoshi|1=Kiyoshi Hasegawa (admiral)}}, then Governor-General of Taiwan.<ref name="潘"/>

